title: US SSN View
description: a read-only display of a US Social Security number
---

{% from "components/united-states-social-security-number-view/macro.njk" import unitedStatesSocialSecurityNumberView %}

<h2>Automatic grouping</h2>
<p>A 9-digit value (with or without spaces or hyphens) is grouped as
  <code>XXX-XX-XXXX</code>.</p>

<dl>
  <dt>Raw 9 digits</dt>
  <dd>{{ unitedStatesSocialSecurityNumberView({ value: "123456789", label: "SSN" }) }}</dd>
  <dt>With hyphens</dt>
  <dd>{{ unitedStatesSocialSecurityNumberView({ value: "123-45-6789", label: "SSN" }) }}</dd>
</dl>

<h2>Masked last-4 pattern</h2>
<p>Consumers commonly mask the leading digits before rendering.
  Values that are not exactly 9 digits render as-is, preserving
  whatever mask characters the consumer supplied:</p>
<p>{{ unitedStatesSocialSecurityNumberView({ value: "XXX-XX-6789", label: "SSN (last 4)" }) }}</p>
